Articles.Content:
Hi all.

Even though I am using visual and building mods I don't think they could affect my output_log so I have put this in the unmodded thread.

 In trying to fix an issue with editor extensions it seems that my output log is giving an incorrect KSP version..

 I am using KSP version 1.2.1 I am 100% sure of this. Here is a screengrab of my start menu:

 

Except the log seems to say 1.1... I have now only one KSP install and I am getting the log from KSP_x64_data folder..

 Here is the log: https://1drv.ms/t/s!Aiprr8BD-R0yggfBsPeTop7d8oT5

Can anyone shed light on this odd issue?

Thanks all.

MJ

Edited November 4, 2016 by Majorjim!

The game gets the version from one of the asset files in KSP_Data, possibly you still have an old one or a mod has changed something it shouldn't have.

Please retest with a clean 1.2.1 install
This is a non issue, can someone close this please?
Okay, but it'd be good to know what's going on.
